5l.title: Complexity of Value
5l.text:
Clickbait:  Normative value is algorithmically complex: there is no simple way to describe the thing we should want AIs to want.

# Truth condition

The 'Complexity of Value' proposition is true if, relative to viable real-world [methodologies] for AI development, there isn't any knowable way to directly specify by hand the AI's [object-level preferences] as a structure of low [algorithmic complexity], and let the result of running that AI being the achievement of [enough of the possible value].
